+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **Stage 3: Forensic Questions --- What a Good Log Enables**           |
|                                                                       |
| *Five questions a SOC analyst must be able to answer from log data    |
| alone*                                                                |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
          **Forensic Question**   **Which Log Field Answers     **Why It Matters for BBC
                                  It**                          Incident Response**
  ------- ----------------------- ----------------------------- -------------------------
  **1**   **When exactly did the  \"timestamp\" on first and    Determines the breach
          attack begin and end?** last LOGIN_FAILURE events     window --- which user
                                                                actions during that
                                                                period need review.
                                                                Required for ICO 72-hour
                                                                breach notification
                                                                timing.

  **2**   **Which account(s) were \"username\" field on every   Identifies whether a
          targeted?**             authentication event          specific high-privilege
                                                                account was targeted
                                                                (e.g. admin, service
                                                                accounts) vs. a broad
                                                                credential-stuffing
                                                                attack.

  **3**   **Did any attempt       \"success\": true in a        Determines whether a data
          succeed?**              LOGIN_SUCCESS event following breach occurred. A
                                  failures                      successful login after 50
                                                                failures is an almost
                                                                certain indicator of
                                                                compromise.

  **4**   **How many attempts     COUNT of events where         Distinguishes a targeted
          were made?**            \"event\"=\"LOGIN_FAILURE\"   manual attack (5--20
                                  and \"source_ip\" matches     attempts) from automated
                                                                credential stuffing
                                                                (thousands). Informs the
                                                                response priority.

  **5**   **Is this the same      \"source_ip\"                 A known-bad IP appearing
          attacker as a previous  cross-referenced against      in logs confirms
          incident?**             threat intelligence feeds     attribution and may
                                                                indicate a persistent
                                                                threat actor rather than
                                                                an opportunistic scan.
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **Now apply this to Juice Shop:**                                     |
|                                                                       |
| -   In Juice Shop, find the \"Access Log\" challenge --- it           |
|     demonstrates what Juice Shop does and does not log.               |
|                                                                       |
| -   Use ZAP to run 20 failed login attempts against Juice Shop\'s     |
|     /rest/user/login endpoint. Check whether Juice Shop surfaces any  |
|     alerting in its UI or admin panel.                                |
|                                                                       |
| -   Compare: what does Juice Shop log vs. what the Module 11 Flask    |
|     structured logging produces? Which gives a SOC analyst more to    |
|     work with?                                                        |
|                                                                       |
| -   Juice Shop\'s \"Forged Feedback\" and \"Five-Star Feedback\"      |
|     challenges both leave no server-side audit trail. What event      |
|     types are missing from Juice Shop\'s log model?                   |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **The A09 test:** after an incident, can you answer --- who was
  attacked, when, from where, how many times, and did it succeed ---
  using only your log files? **If the answer to any of those five
  questions is \"cannot tell,\" you have an A09 failure.** The fix is not
  a SIEM. The fix is structured security events at the application layer.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
